Overall the Sandbox seems best positioned to become the leading Metaverse. Although still early, the Sandbox has the backing of celebrities and cooperations, which may prove to be valuable in the future.

#Decentraland is one of the first created metaverses. Also backed by a large community, Decentraland is home to several large events such as the Metaverse Fashion Week.

A weakness is that larger cooperations generally tend to choose the Sandbox to enter the Metaverse.

NFT Worlds is one of the most hyped projects. In February the floor quadrupled! 

Unique about NFT Worlds is that it is built upon Minecraft. Problematic however is that NFT Worlds doesn't have a full commercial license from Microsoft. Currently the game-token $WRLD is airdropped

The #Sandbox is probably the most known metaverse. Not only does it have a large community, but has also attracted large cooperate brands: Adidas, Gucci, BAYC, RTFKT. An extremely bullish sign!

Currently the Sandbox hasn't launched, however the alpha season seems very promising.

There is currently a lot of hype around NFT metaverses. The Sandbox, NFT Worlds, Decentraland... But who is actually the frontrunner? Here are my thoughts:

Generally when analyzing projects I apply the UCTA formula:

Utility: What benefits does hodling provide? Roadmap?
Community: How engaged and active?
Team: Are the founder's visionaries? Regular updates?
Art: Does the art appeal to me?

Most importantly never forget - nfts are illiquid assets. Therefore: YOU NEED TO LIKE THE ART. 

Nothing is more painful than sitting on art that you don‚Äôt even like.

When analyzing a project look for these 3 MUST HAVES:

1. An engaging community. This is essential. Community creates demand and hype. Without a community a project is worthless.

2. Utility and roadmap. There needs to be some incentive to hodl.

3. Community engaging founders.

99% of all #nft projects are scam. Especially rn many new projects are entering the space promising ‚Äúthe moon.‚Äù ‚ùå

It has never been more important to look for quality NFTs. Thorough analysis is crucial.
